thread.title: U.S. Dollar Down on Tariff Concerns

author: wsjcom
title: U.S. Dollar Down on Tariff Concerns
text:
The dollar reversed gains Thursday as investors grew concerned about the effect of new steel and aluminum tariffs on the U.S. currency.
The WSJ Dollar Index, which measures the U.S. currency against a basket of 16 others, was recently down 0.3% at 83.99. It had risen as high as 84.46 earlier in the session.
